{"legislative_session": "2025A", "identifier": "SB25-320", "title": "Commercial Motor Vehicle Transportation", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": [], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Joint Budget Committee. Prior to January 1, 2025, certain low-emitting  heavy-duty motor vehicles, vehicle power sources, and parts for vehicle power source conversion which met specified federal or state law requirements related to greenhouse gas emission reduction were exempt from state sales and use tax. Section 1  of the bill reinstates the tax exemption for the period beginning on and after August 1, 2025, but prior to January 1, 2029, and clarifies the intent of the tax expenditure. Section 2 increases the amount of the bridge and tunnel impact fee (fee) to be imposed per gallon of special fuel by the statewide bridge and tunnel enterprise from $0.05 per gallon to $0.07 per gallon for state fiscal year 2025-26, from $0.06 per gallon to $0.07 per gallon for state fiscal year 2026-27, and from $0.07 per gallon to $0.08 per gallon for state fiscal year 2027-28. Section 3 makes an appropriation.\n(Note: Italicized words indicate new material added to the original summary; dashes through words indicate deletions from the original summary.)\n(Note: This summary applies to the reengrossed version of this bill as introduced in the second house.)"}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Signed by the Speaker of the House", "date": "2025-05-13T06:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Signed by the President of the Senate", "date": "2025-05-13T06:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Sent to the Governor", "date": "2025-05-13T06:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"executive